 worse mines will step up to produce coal to replace the stuff you take out=
 of circulation, etc. In some ways this strategy works better with big symb=
olic policy changes at household names like McDonald=E2=80=99s than it does=
 with commodity producers, but the big symbolic companies are expensive.[2]=
 Unless you=E2=80=99ve been there for a long time and retire or otherwise l=
eave banking. Though that is changing: =E2=80=9CInside Goldman, a tradition=
 known as the Rule of 60 lets executives keep their deferred stock if the s=
um of their age and tenure at the firm exceeds 60. It=E2=80=99s a way to re=
ward long-time employees who decide to take a run at another career. Throug=
