<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">ESG M&amp;A</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/26805474.278600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDItMjIvYm9yZWQtYXBlcy1nby10by1jb3VydD9jbXBpZD1C=
QkQwMjIzMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHR=
lciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjAyMjMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB16dbb0a6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> talked yesterday</a> about Carl Icahn=E2=80=99s p=
lans to mount a proxy fight at McDonald=E2=80=99s Corp. over its treatment =
of pigs. It is a strange situation. On the one hand, Icahn=E2=80=99s motive=
s seem essentially altruistic and uneconomical: He cares about animal welfa=
re, his daughter <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
6805474.278600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9jYXJsLWljYWhuLW1jZG9u=
YWxkcy1waWdzLWdlc3RhdGlvbi1jcmF0ZXMtMTE2NDQzMzUxOTg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB4662e4de" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">worked at the Humane Society</a> and got him involved, =
he owns only a tiny number of McDonald=E2=80=99s shares and isn=E2=80=99t i=
n it for the money. On the other hand, Icahn is a billionaire and a ruthles=
s corporate raider with a long history of investing millions of dollars in =
scorched-earth proxy fights and winning them. That combination is unusual.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But with the higher profile of environmenta=
l, social and governance investing, you would expect to see more stuff=C2=
=A0<em>like=C2=A0</em>this. There are a lot of rich people who care about E=
SG issues, proxy-fight expertise can be hired, and there are probably more =
cases where mounting a public-company proxy fight is a decent use of a few =
million dollars to achieve some environmental or social aim.=C2=A0</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, to win a proxy fight, you need o=
ther shareholders to vote with you. Lots of shareholders care about ESG the=
se days, so you have the wind at your back, but you still need to make a bu=
siness case to them to have a realistic shot. =E2=80=9CMcDonald=E2=80=99s s=
hould treat pigs better to avoid a customer backlash that would reduce sale=
s=E2=80=9D is fine, but =E2=80=9CMcDonald=E2=80=99s should permanently sacr=
ifice profits for the good of pigs=E2=80=9D is not a good pitch to sharehol=
ders even if both you and the BlackRock Inc. governance specialist covering=
 McDonald=E2=80=99s happen to believe it. Fortunately it is a pretty standa=
rd form of ESG argument to say =E2=80=9Cdoing this thing that is good for t=
he environment will also be good for cash flows in the long run,=E2=80=9D a=
nd Engine No. 1 LLC=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/26805474.278600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvZXh4b24tbG9zdC1hLWNsaW1hdGUtcHJveHktZmlnaHQ_Y21waW=
Q9QkJEMDIyMzIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZ=
XR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMjIzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB90b4a595" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> proxy fight at Exxon Mobil Corp. last year</=
a>=C2=A0shows that those forms of argument can be used to win a proxy fight=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have a=C2=A0<em>lot=C2=A0</em>of m=
oney, though, you can sort of circumvent this problem. Never mind a proxy f=
ight; do a hostile takeover offer. Find some public company doing a thing y=
ou don=E2=80=99t like, buy the company, and stop it doing the thing. The pi=
tch to shareholders is not =E2=80=9Cstopping this thing will make you more =
money,=E2=80=9D but rather =E2=80=9CI will just give you more money =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0I will buy your shares at a premium =E2=80=94=C2=A0and then I will=
 stop the company from doing the thing for my own reasons which don=E2=80=
=99t concern you.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not real=
ly feasible=C2=A0with McDonald=E2=80=99s, which has=C2=A0a $190 billion=C2=
=A0market capitalization and=C2=A0does lots of things, only some of which C=
arl Icahn doesn=E2=80=99t like. But you could imagine someone who made bill=
ions of dollars in tech being easily able to afford, say, a <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26805474.278600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9xdW90ZS9DRUlYOlVTP3NyZWY9MWtKVk5xblU/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB448dc4b3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">thermal coal miner</a>, or a <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26805474.278600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9xdW90ZS9BT1VUOlVTP3NyZWY9MWtKVk5xblU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB820=
94049" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">gun manufacturer</a>. You buy it, you shut down the coal min=
es, you keep the employees on for a few years to plant trees on the coal mi=
nes and=C2=A0retrain to be blockchain engineers.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">This is probably not the best bang for your buck in philanthropy or a=
nything,[1] but it might have some positive externalities. Other companies =
with bad ESG records will have to think not just =E2=80=9Cif we continue to=
 have bad ESG records, ESG funds will dump our stock, slightly depressing o=
ur stock price, and our large index-fund holders will come in every quarter=
 and make sad faces at us,=E2=80=9D but also =E2=80=9Cif we continue to hav=
e bad ESG records some tech billionaire will buy us out, fire all the execu=
tives and plant flowers in our factories.=E2=80=9D Expanding the toolkit of=
=C2=A0<em>coercive=C2=A0</em>ESG strategies =E2=80=94=C2=A0not just asking =
executives nicely to be better at ESG, but firing them if they say no =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0can be a way to accelerate good ESG behavior in public companie=
s generally, even if you rarely use the coercive tools.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">Anyway this isn=E2=80=99t really that, <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26805474.278600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc21oLmNvb=
S5hdS9idXNpbmVzcy9jb21wYW5pZXMvaW5zaWRlLXByb2plY3QtYXJpc2UtY2Fubm9uLWJyb29r=
ZXMtc2VjcmV0LXBsYW4tdG8tdGFrZS1vdmVyLWFnbC0yMDIyMDIyMS1wNTl5ZXIuaHRtbA/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6daf79e5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">but it=E2=80=99s fascinating</a>:</p=
><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Late last year, as world leaders =
entered the final stages of negotiations for emissions targets they would m=
ake at COP26 climate summit in Glasgow, a small team had formed in Australi=
a plotting what could turn out to be one of the single largest decarbonisat=
ion projects the world had yet seen.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The te=
am called itself Project Arise =E2=80=93 a partnership between the Australi=
an software billionaire Mike Cannon-Brookes and his wife Annie=E2=80=99s pr=
ivate investment vehicle Grok Ventures and Canadian asset manager Brookfiel=
d, a corporate behemoth with a track record of serious energy and infrastru=
cture investing.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Project Arise was secretly=
 assessing making an offer to buy AGL, the largest Australian power company=
. Part of its ambitious proposal would be to fast-track the company=E2=80=
=99s plans to close its fleet of coal-fired power stations and invest an ex=
traordinary $10-20 billion in projects to replace them, including with wind=
 farms and big batteries.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For years, Cannon=
-Brookes, the co-founder of Atlassian and Australia=E2=80=99s third richest=
 person, had made his frustration at Australia=E2=80=99s lumbering climate =
politics and lack of meaningful action abundantly clear. ...</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Cannon-Brookes has become a prominent investor in renewab=
le energy, including plans to develop the world=E2=80=99s largest solar far=
m in the Northern Territory and link it via an underwater cable to Singapor=
e.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, he started thinking about what =
more his money could do for the planet. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">The ambitious offer for AGL was lobbed on Saturday. It valued the co=
mpany at $8 billion, with another $10 billion to $20 billion promised to ba=
nkroll a new fleet of renewable energy including wind farms and big batteri=
es that would help replace AGL=E2=80=99s coal-fired power stations and brin=
g forward their retirement to as early as 2030, 15 years sooner than the co=
mpany=E2=80=99s current plans.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>The plan here is obviously to earn a financial return; Cannon-Brookes=E2=
=80=99s motivations might be partly or entirely altruistic but Brookfield i=
s a business. The goal is to buy a polluting power company and accelerate i=
ts transition to being a less-polluting power company that is economically =
viable for the long term, not to buy it and shut it down and write off the =
$8 billion purchase price.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But that is a st=
andard ESG move: Make changes that are good for the environment, and also m=
ake a case that they are good for sustainable long-term shareholder returns=
. The Exxon proxy fight showed that those sorts of=C2=A0arguments can win t=
he support of public shareholders in a proxy fight. Apparently they can als=
o raise the money=C2=A0for a takeover.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponso=
